description: Retrieve the results of a predictive inbox placement test.

parameters.name: ReportId
parameters.description: A unique string that identifies the predictive inbox placement test.

nested_items.name: DeliverabilityTestReport
nested_items.description: An object that contains the results of the predictive inbox placement test.

nested_items.name: ReportId
nested_items.description: A unique string that identifies the predictive inbox placement test.

nested_items.name: ReportName
nested_items.description: A name that helps you identify a predictive inbox placement test report.

nested_items.name: Subject
nested_items.description: The subject line for an email that you submitted in a predictive inbox placement test.

nested_items.name: FromEmailAddress
nested_items.description: The sender address that you specified for the predictive inbox placement test.

nested_items.name: CreateDate
nested_items.description: The date and time when the predictive inbox placement test was created, in Unix time format.

nested_items.name: DeliverabilityTestStatus
nested_items.description: The status of the predictive inbox placement test. If the status is IN_PROGRESS, then the predictive inbox placement test is currently running. Predictive inbox placement tests are usually complete within 24 hours of creating the test. If the status is COMPLETE, then the test is finished, and you can use the GetDeliverabilityTestReport to view the results of the test.

nested_items.name: OverallPlacement
nested_items.description: An object that specifies how many test messages that were sent during the predictive inbox placement test were delivered to recipients' inboxes, how many were sent to recipients' spam folders, and how many weren't delivered.

nested_items.name: InboxPercentage
nested_items.description: The percentage of emails that arrived in recipients' inboxes during the predictive inbox placement test.

nested_items.name: SpamPercentage
nested_items.description: The percentage of emails that arrived in recipients' spam or junk mail folders during the predictive inbox placement test.

nested_items.name: MissingPercentage
nested_items.description: The percentage of emails that didn't arrive in recipients' inboxes at all during the predictive inbox placement test.

nested_items.name: SpfPercentage
nested_items.description: The percentage of emails that were authenticated by using Sender Policy Framework (SPF) during the predictive inbox placement test.

nested_items.name: DkimPercentage
nested_items.description: The percentage of emails that were authenticated by using DomainKeys Identified Mail (DKIM) during the predictive inbox placement test.

nested_items.name: IspPlacements
nested_items.description: An object that describes how the test email was handled by several email providers, including Gmail, Hotmail, Yahoo, AOL, and others.

nested_items.name: IspName
nested_items.description: The name of the email provider that the inbox placement data applies to.

nested_items.name: PlacementStatistics
nested_items.description: An object that contains inbox placement metrics for a specific email provider.

nested_items.name: InboxPercentage
nested_items.description: The percentage of emails that arrived in recipients' inboxes during the predictive inbox placement test.

nested_items.name: SpamPercentage
nested_items.description: The percentage of emails that arrived in recipients' spam or junk mail folders during the predictive inbox placement test.

nested_items.name: MissingPercentage
nested_items.description: The percentage of emails that didn't arrive in recipients' inboxes at all during the predictive inbox placement test.

nested_items.name: SpfPercentage
nested_items.description: The percentage of emails that were authenticated by using Sender Policy Framework (SPF) during the predictive inbox placement test.

nested_items.name: DkimPercentage
nested_items.description: The percentage of emails that were authenticated by using DomainKeys Identified Mail (DKIM) during the predictive inbox placement test.

nested_items.name: Message
nested_items.description: An object that contains the message that you sent when you performed this predictive inbox placement test.

nested_items.name: Tags
nested_items.description: An array of objects that define the tags (keys and values) that are associated with the predictive inbox placement test.
Tag keys and values are case sensitive.
For each associated resource, each tag key must be unique and it can have only one value.

TheÂ  aws:Â prefix is reserved for use by AWS; you can't use it in any tag keys or values that you define. In addition, you can't edit or remove tag keys or values that use this prefix. Tags that use this prefix don't count against the limit of 50 tags per resource.

You can associate tags with public or shared resources, but the tags are available only for your AWS account, not any other accounts that share the resource. In addition, the tags are available only for resources that are located in the specified AWS Region for your AWS account.
